Second Lady Karen Pence has been traveling to National Parks in order to promote the mental health benefits of spending time outdoors. She emphasizes that studies have shown that being outside can help reduce stress, anxiety, and the risk of depression. Mrs. Pence encourages Americans to acknowledge their struggles and to not be afraid to admit when they are not okay. She also expresses gratitude towards National Park employees for their work in maintaining the parks during the pandemic and reopening them in a safe manner. Mrs. Pence began her visits in May, which is Mental Health Awareness Month, and has continued to highlight parks as places of respite. She also stresses the importance of checking in with oneself and loved ones during these challenging times.